 have been\nflattened. Two species are exceptions to this behaviour, namely Al and Si,\nwhich both clearly display remaining trends in the non-LTE analysis. We comment\non the possible origin of these trends, by comparing them with recent stellar\nmodels that include atomic diffusion.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 17 Apr 2018 17:39:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 23 Aug 2018 07:23:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-09-12"}
